6 Hours Ago “It is true, but the information is not still clear. It is not true that several security men lost their lives. About two security men on duty at the governor’s house were killed. NSCDC personnel was among the security men who lost their lives during the attack,” he said. The incident is coming few days after unknown gunmen attacked the police headquarters and the correctional centre in Owerri, Imo State, setting 38 vehicles ablaze and freeing 1,844 inmates. Police stations have also come under attack in the region, with many officers killed. South-East governors recently announced a joint security outfit, codenamed ‘Ebube Agu’ to battle rising insecurity.